{"id":13654,"date":"2024-02-17T18:23:03","date_gmt":"2020-08-17T12:53:03","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=13654"},"modified":"2024-02-01T16:47:55","modified_gmt":"2024-02-01T11:17:55","slug":"bright-room-colours","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/bright-room-colours\/","title":{"rendered":"Bright Room Colour Ideas To Brighten Up Your Home!"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Here\u2019s a lowdown of bright room colour ideas to breathe in some life in your room and make it look bright and vibrant!&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bright colours have the power to command attention due to both their shade and brightness! Warm colours &#8211;&nbsp; yellows, reds and oranges &#8211; are brighter than cold colour tones such as blues and greens. Shades of browns and greys aren&#8217;t as bright unless they are incredibly muted almost next to being white.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We all know that the colour of your space can significantly affect the vibe of the room it&#8217;s used in whether it&#8217;s a sunny shade of yellow or a soothing blue. While pastel and neutral colours can make a small room look more spacious deeper, bolder tones can also make a room look bright<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Today we bring you some of the most stunning bright room colour ideas for your home let&#8217;s get started!<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Brightest Colour Of All, Yellow<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Yellow is a bright colour that can make any room look pleasant in your home especially in common areas like the living or dining room. This is one such colour that can go literally everywhere and on everything! From accent walls to upholstery, and from furniture to decor. When paired with more subtle colours like beige and white, yellow brings in much-needed brightness to a space. Yellow is the perfect bright colour if you wish to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/living-room-design\/\">design your living room<\/a> with wooden furniture.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17175617\/bright-room-colors-of-all-yellow-with-bright-living-room-colors.jpg\" alt=\"Bright yellow room colors for your home which adds much needed brightness to a space\" class=\"wp-image-13656\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17175617\/bright-room-colors-of-all-yellow-with-bright-living-room-colors.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17175617\/bright-room-colors-of-all-yellow-with-bright-living-room-colors-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17175617\/bright-room-colors-of-all-yellow-with-bright-living-room-colors-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17175617\/bright-room-colors-of-all-yellow-with-bright-living-room-colors-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, check out <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/yellow-living-room-colour-ideas\/\">Yellow Living Room Colours<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">A Statement Bright Orange<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A splash of bright orange can instantly make a room look active and vibrant. Be it your living room, any bedroom or even a study area. This bright colour tone adds a sense of liveliness making it an ideal choice for a room where there&#8217;s no space for dullness like a study room, and common areas where an inviting vibe is a must! We recommend you to use this colour in a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/kids-bedroom-design\/\">kids bedroom<\/a> where fun and studies go hand in hand. If a complete orange room scares you, you can always add a statement wall in orange and remaining walls in a neutral shade. Or you can go for a lighter shade of orange.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17175857\/bright-color-combinations-with-orange.jpg\" alt=\"Statement bright orange color which adds a sense of liveliness\" class=\"wp-image-13658\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17175857\/bright-color-combinations-with-orange.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17175857\/bright-color-combinations-with-orange-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17175857\/bright-color-combinations-with-orange-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17175857\/bright-color-combinations-with-orange-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Bright Navy For Your Home<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Like other deep colours, navy instantly makes a room feel cosier making it the right pick for a bedroom. Here, in this uber-stylish bedroom, a bright navy statement wall adds the required colour pop to an otherwise neutral colour scheme. A bright colour like this one will work great in a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/guides\/master-bedroom-design-ideas\/\">master bedroom<\/a> or a guest bedroom as it adds much-needed brightness ultimately making the room feel more cosy and intimate.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180225\/bright-bedroom-colors-with-navy.jpg\" alt=\"Bright navy colour for your bedroom which adds the required colour pop\" class=\"wp-image-13659\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180225\/bright-bedroom-colors-with-navy.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180225\/bright-bedroom-colors-with-navy-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180225\/bright-bedroom-colors-with-navy-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180225\/bright-bedroom-colors-with-navy-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Instagram worthy home interiors that will steal your heart!\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/11\/03181146\/instagram-worthy-home-interiors-that-will-steal-your-heart.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">A Coat Of Inviting Bright Green<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Green is the colour that adds peace and rejuvenation not to mention it echoes nature! It&#8217;s an excellent paint colour for areas like living or dining rooms. If you are tight on space, don&#8217;t have a garden or a huge balcony for a bevvy of indoor plants a green wall will add a dash of life to your living room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180352\/bright-wall-colors-inviting-bright-green.jpg\" alt=\"Bright green wall colors that adds peace and rejuvenation\" class=\"wp-image-13660\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180352\/bright-wall-colors-inviting-bright-green.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180352\/bright-wall-colors-inviting-bright-green-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180352\/bright-wall-colors-inviting-bright-green-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180352\/bright-wall-colors-inviting-bright-green-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, check out <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/green-living-room-ideas\/\">Green Living Room Ideas<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Chic Bright Coral<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Coral is a colour that&#8217;s all the rage these days as it&#8217;s a subtle yet bright colour that accentuates decors in bold colours. It compliments cobalt blue, greys and white well giving any room a fresh and lively vibe. For a bit of bling coral or pastel pink can be paired with light grey, white, smokey blue and copper. This combination is modern and works well with designs that are minimal or neo-classical. Coral is a colour that is ideal for bedrooms, studyroom, kitchens and bathrooms.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180601\/chic-bright-coral-colour-list.jpg\" alt=\"Chic bright coral colour for your home that accentuates decors in bold colours\" class=\"wp-image-13661\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180601\/chic-bright-coral-colour-list.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180601\/chic-bright-coral-colour-list-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180601\/chic-bright-coral-colour-list-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180601\/chic-bright-coral-colour-list-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Striking Teal Or Peacock Blue<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Teal is another bright colour that is fresh and bold. It pairs well with white, baby pinks and gold accents. This colour is best suited for those looking for an eclectic interior style. Teal is a great backdrop colour, especially for large walls to showcase furniture decor that is quirky and unique. Teal works well in a living, family and dining area as this bright and loud colour is ideal for common spaces with lots of people and energy.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180829\/striking-teal-or-peacock-blue-bright-paint-colors.jpg\" alt=\"Striking teal or peacock blue color for for large walls which adds freshness to the space\" class=\"wp-image-13662\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180829\/striking-teal-or-peacock-blue-bright-paint-colors.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180829\/striking-teal-or-peacock-blue-bright-paint-colors-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180829\/striking-teal-or-peacock-blue-bright-paint-colors-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/17180829\/striking-teal-or-peacock-blue-bright-paint-colors-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For these colours to really stand out to make your room look bright and vibrant make sure you incorporate perfect lighting! Pick brighter lights for common areas and softer lights for bedrooms to highlight the details and level up the brightness of the space!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope these stunning bright room colour ideas help you design a room that is bright and inviting!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Happy decorating!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore, More About<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/blue-wall-paint-colours\/\">Blue Wall Paint colours<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/white-living-room-design\/\">White Living Room Designs<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/brown-wall-paint-colours\/\">Brown Wall 